ern Paci\nfic railroad for the year ended De\ncember 31 showed a net loss of 83,-\n450.365 against a net loss of 82.421.114\nin 1936.\nGotham Silk Hosiery company re\nported net income of $351,159 for\n1937, equal to 40 cents a share on\nthe common stock after dividend re\nquirements on the $7 cumulative\npreferred stock. This com pates with\nearnings of $405,651 or 54 cents a\nshare in 1936.\nChesapeake coi poration. the C. A O.\nhold^ig company, declared a dividend\ncf 75 cents a share payable April\n2 to shareholders of March 8. ths\nw.me as the precedes carter. C.\nO. reported net O* $1,335,409\nfor January, after all charges, a\ndecrease of $229,446 from January,\n1937.\nCuban exports of sugar from Jan\nuary 1 to February 12 totaled 258.949\nImg tons, raw value, compared with\n274 915 tons in the comparable 193 T\nperiod, a decrease of about 5.8 per\ncent.\nKennecott Copper declared a divi\ndend of 25 cents a share on the\ncapital stock, payable March 31 to\nholders of record February 26.\nUnited Carbon reported for 193 T\nnet profit of $2,350,486. equal to\n$.,.9# a common share compaied with\n$2,202,850. or $5.54 in 1936.\nGeneral Raking reported a net\nprofit of $1,504,113, equal to 50 centa\na share, for the year ended December\n31. This compares with $2,611,839\nor $1.20 on the common in 1936,\nCongoleum Nairn. Inc., a leading\nproducer of llmieum and base floor\ncovering, reported net income for\n1937 of $2,324 '129. or $2.03 a common\nshare, compared with $2,548,689 or\n$2.05 in 1936.\nNet sales, royalties and other op\nerating revenues of the Owens-Illinois\nGlass company and subsidiary com\npanies in the year ended December\n31. 1937. amounted to $91.581003 m\ncompared to $78,713,827 In 1936. stock\nholders were informed yesterday tn\nthe yearly report. Net income for 1937\nwas $9,351,627 as compared to $lO.-\n099.131 In 1936.\nNewmont Mining company declared\na dividend of 50 cents a share on the\ncapital stock, payable March 15 to\nholders of record 